Today, the Democratic Alliance (DA) #PowerToThePeopleMarch to Luthuli House took place. The march created a movement which saw people protesting around the country, against the damage caused by loadshedding, due to corruption and mismanagement. Well-known activist and businessman Rob Hersov attended the march in Johannesburg and had major support from protestors. DA leader John Steenhuisen stated: “”Only your vote can reclaim your power from the crooks in Luthuli House.” Those who attended the march have described it as powerful and uniting South Africans who want to create a better future. 